    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-02T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-02T05:00:00-05:00" n="60"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6315/1: Telegram (part air)</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Earle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-02T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 2, 1934—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 4—1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. Stockinger, Minister of Commerce, informs me that in order to expand Austrian
                    foreign trade the Government will send special missions abroad. One will soon
                    leave for the Scandinavian countries and within a fortnight another one to the
                    United States. He added that the purpose of this mission was to sell such
                    Austrian goods as did not compete with American and above all not to dump
                    goods.</p>
                <p>I am of the opinion that the real purpose of these missions is political; first,
                    to further Austrian independence of Germany and, second, to demonstrate to the
                    Austrian people the Government’s activity in relieving the economic
                    distress.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Earle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
